Both practices are customary during the fasting month of Ramadan, with retreats taking place in the last 10 days of the month. Religious Affairs Minister Mohammad Mokhtar Gom'a had said the ban was designed to avoid spreading coronavirus. But Muslims in Egypt demanded equality with Christians who have been gathering in large numbers to celebrate Easter this week. A hashtag trending on Twitter on Tuesday described Egyptian President Abdul Fattah al-Sisi as an "enemy of God". --BBC--